In days long forgotten, the ancestors of cheetahs were among the first to lay with the race of man. However unlike the other "Domesticated" anthros, at some point they were forced to return to the wilds, the shared history between man and cheetah fading into myth and then being forgotten entirely. But their bodies didn't forget, for the heart of every cheetah pumps a tiny bit of human blood through their veins, a relic of days long past that the mind has forgotten, but the body refuses to. To them, unlike other "Wild" anthros, a human doesn't represent some strange and new thing, but an old friend. It's also the reason why wolf girls like humans so much and why wolves and cheetahs always seem to get along weirdly well.
